  "prompt": "How do I take admission in JNU?",
  "response": "To take admission in Jawaharlal Nehru University (JNU), follow these steps:\n\n1. Online Application Process:\n- Visit the official JNU website (jnu.ac.in)\n- Register and fill the online application form\n- Select the desired course/program\n\n2. Entrance Examination:\n- Appear for JNU Entrance Examination (JNUEE)\n- Different entrance exams for different programs\n- Conducted usually in December/January\n\n3. Eligibility Criteria:\n- Must have relevant undergraduate/postgraduate degree\n- Minimum qualifying marks as per university norms\n- Age limit varies by program\n\n4. Required Documents:\n- Mark sheets\n- Degree certificates\n- Category certificate (if applicable)\n- Transfer/migration certificate\n- Character certificate\n- Passport size photographs\n\n5. Selection Process:\n- Based on JNUEE entrance exam score\n- Merit list will be published\n- Called for counseling/interview\n\n6. Important Tips:\n- Check official website for updated information\n- Follow application deadlines\n- Prepare well for entrance examination\n- Keep documents ready\n\nRecommended to regularly check JNU's official website for precise and current admission guidelines.",
